Class School

  • java.lang.Object
    • School

  • public class School
extends java.lang.Object
    Creates a school object with a List of Zones. Each Zone contains a list of Students. Additionally contains methods to load all the appropriate zones from a file, as well as all of the students in each zone from a file. Can move students from one zone to another and write the changes to disk.
    Since:
    9-15-2020
    Version:
    2.0
    Author:
    Madeline Kotara - duk128

      • loadZones

        public void loadZones(java.lang.String filePath)
               throws java.io.IOException
        Creates a zone by reading the contents of a file from disk. Uses data from each column to create a zone object and then adds the new zone object to the List of Zones. repeats until end of file is reached.
        Parameters:
        filePath - Requires the string path of the file on disk
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - throws an exception if the path is invalid, or the file was not found

      • loadStudents

        public void loadStudents(java.lang.String filePath)
                  throws java.io.IOException
        Creates the appropriate list of students within the appropriate Zone. Uses data from each column to create a student, then matches the student's zone code with the zone's actual code and adds the student to that Array. Repeats until end of file is reached.
        Parameters:
        filePath - Requires the string path of the file on disk
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - throws an exception if the path is invalid, or the file was not found

        zoneCode - The zoneCode that the student should be moved to
